---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Founding Partner Waitlist | AI Training Directory"
  description="Join the founding partner waitlist for AI Training Directory visibility opportunities before paid placements open."
  canonical="https://aitraining.directory/advertise/"
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Founding Partners', href: '/advertise/' }]} />
  <h1>Founding partner interest (pre-launch)</h1>
  <p class="muted">We are prioritizing audience quality and category relevance before turning on self-serve paid placements.</p>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>Waitlist: Sponsored Category Slots</h2>
      <p>Reserve early access for category sponsorship opportunities when traffic benchmarks are hit.</p>
      <p><a href="mailto:sales@aitraining.directory?subject=Founding%20Partner%20Waitlist">Join waitlist</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Founding Partner Program</h2>
      <p>Best for L&D-focused platforms that want launch visibility plus positioning input on category pages.</p>
      <p><a href="mailto:sales@aitraining.directory?subject=Founding%20Partner%20Interest">Submit interest</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>DFY Listing Optimization</h2>
      <p>Optional advisory service for positioning, copy upgrades, and internal link strategy once volume is live.</p>
      <p><a href="mailto:sales@aitraining.directory?subject=Listing%20Optimization%20Interest">Request details</a></p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <h2>Monetization path (documented, not hard-sold)</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Phase 1: Waitlist capture + qualification</li>
    <li>Phase 2: Invite-only sponsored slots after baseline organic demand is proven</li>
    <li>Phase 3: Public media kit and transparent placement guidelines</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Need invoicing or procurement details?</h2>
  <p>Email <a href="mailto:sales@aitraining.directory">sales@aitraining.directory</a>.</p>
</Base>
